DURBAN - A grandmother and her two grandchildren were rescued unharmed after an armed robber held them hostage in their home in uMbumbulu, south of Durban on Tuesday.Police said that a group of armed suspects robbed a business in Cato Ridge on Tuesday and authorities responded to the scene, and gave chase. The suspects separated after they crashed their vehicle in uMbumbulu and one of the suspects fled into a nearby home and held the family hostage. Explaining the sequence of events, provincial police spokesperson Brigadier Jay Naicker said the business robbery occurred at 10.30am.He said five men entered a cellphone shop and robbed the staff at gunpoint.“The suspects stole a large number of cellphones before fleeing the scene in their getaway vehicle,” he said.MORE ON THISStore manager arrested for staging a robbery at his shopDurbanville family survive nightmare house robberyGateway mall insists security has been beefed after yet another jewellery store robberyGrandma aged 80, her daughter and son-in-law assaulted in robbery at Limpopo farmNaicker said Magma Security & Investigations was contacted and they immediately responded to the scene before alerting police.The suspects fled towards uMbumbulu, he said.“On a dirt road, the suspects lost control of their vehicle. They alighted from their vehicle whilst firing shots at responding officers,” said Naicker.He said one of the suspects was arrested while the others ran into bushes.At this point, police officers from the K9 Unit and Special Task Force joined the chase, he said.Naicker said one of the suspects fled into a nearby house and held the occupants hostage.“After a lengthy stand-off, with the assistance of the hostage negotiators, the suspect was apprehended and his firearm was seized. The grandmother and her two young grandchildren who were held hostage were released unharmed,” he said.Naicker said three suspects are still in the bushes and are being pursued by police officers and the K9 Unit.THE MERCURY